##PET RESCUE IN WUHAN:'I received the greatest kindness of my life'

Micro-signal. NBWEEKLY

Introduction of function, new media with temperature

People in the city could not get out, people outside the city could not get in, and the remaining Chinese pets faced starvation.

By Xu Jianbao, Zhao Qiong, Zhou Xiaoyu, Wang Chao

Editor | Shen Xiaoshan

After the city closure in Wuhan, in addition to the people left behind, there are countless unattended pets. Some owners have long expected not to come back in time will be released, let the pet to find a way; more owners reluctant to take away, had to leave the pet in Wuhan, the door locked.

Forced separation

"My 17 is my baby girl. She came to Wuhan on November 17,2018, the day before my birthday, so I called her 17. After having 17, every day after work would like to go straight home to take care of her, play with her, will worry about her physical condition. When a person will tell her what happened, will tell her his mind. For me, she's not just a life, she's my family, and we're each other's company,"said Wei Xue (not her real name) , who works in Wuhan.

Every time she has an affair or business trip will put 17 sent in a pet shop, pet shop owner nice, every day and her video call, so that she assured. The pet shop was a big help in the outbreak in Wuhan.

However, many people who leave the Han are not so lucky. Many more had to leave before the city closed before they could properly place their pets.

At 7:32 pm on January 26, Shook posted a message asking for help on a social media platform. "Is there anyone who lives near the Hongshan District neighborhood who would like to visit the cat in the next few days, add water and drink food, so that he won't starve to death? " He asked

When I contacted Shook, she told us: "The cat has been at home for six days, cat food and water estimates to last five or six days, so long not to see him, I still feel a little worried, the key is still in their hands, if you want to find help feed to send the key. ".

January 26, Shook

There are many cases like Shook's in Wuhan. Some owners look for acquaintances, friends to feed, solve the problem. The most difficult thing is that people are not in Wuhan, there are no acquaintances in Wuhan.

About pet self-help

Foshan, Ivan

On Jan. 24, when the situation was dire in Wuhan, Ivan, the owner of the local cat group, and the group's administrator discussed how to resolve the crisis, Ivan decided to organize the group to keep Han pets. Then, Ivan and administrators first on Weibo to remind, and then received a lot of netizens'replies, so began to set up group related issues.

January 24, Wuhan "native Cat Tonghao" micro blog

The price is negotiated between the rescuer and the person asking for help. To prevent the premium, the earthen cat sets a ceiling of 150 for a visit, 150 for two or less, if the cats are more numerous, 50 Bucks more for a cat. Can't Jack up the price.

Taking into account the safety of Pets, "earthen cat" for home feeding people are very strict requirements, must first conduct identity verification, Attach ID card and his recent photos, verification through, can be the next rescue work.

"It's a house call. We don't know each other. We have to think about the safety of cats. That is to say, if you know more about cats, if you are just enthusiastic, but have no experience at all, sometimes it will do you no good. There's also the concern that, after all, we have to be responsible for the safety of the people who are asking for help, and after all, we are connected through us, so we must be responsible,"Ivan said.

Ivan and volunteers come to the house to rescue the remaining Han pets

As of January 27,646 people had sought help from the indigenous cat community and 96 people had come to their homes to help. The number of people who had completed the docking and mutual assistance was about 200 to 300.

To the masses... as if it were a dream

At 1:30 pm on January 25, So Meng created the first feeding group, in which local people from Wuhan help pet owners who are not in Wuhan to feed animals. At 3:30 p.m. , the group of people far exceeded the expectations of the dream, so she asked the Wuhan Small Animal Association for help. It was pleasant, so I agreed with Du Fan, President of Wuhan Animals Association, to do something to help the "Mao children" .

On January 26th, the gang has had a small impact. Dozens of groups have been formed, including the Wuhan Guanggu Gang Feed Group, the Wuchang Gang Feed Group, the Tibetan Dragon Island Group Feed Group, the Hankou Gang Feed Group and the Hanyang Gang Feed Group, and thousands of people have joined in the mutual aid campaign.

January 27, Wuhan Guanggu Gang Feed Group

"The group was set up mainly thanks to especially kind-hearted people. To help is really pure kindness. " The old dream says that some of them have a car, some don't, and some just ride their bikes all over Wuhan, on shuttle in Wuhan's "far south, far north" , someone completely free to help others feed the pet, the maximum charge is also 30-50 yuan.

In some of the houses that needed to be unlocked, the volunteers would leave the video and the pet owner on the line, and the volunteer would ask the company's master to open the door under the supervision of the householder. The longer the city remains closed, the more pets will be left to be fed.

"these days I receive the most intensive kindness in my life, " the old dream said.

After the closure of the city, many clean, very beautiful stray animals, a look that is recently abandoned. Videos of these strays are often seen in feeding groups. So the dream said, "in fact, these animals can be sent to a pet hospital or find someone else to adopt, do not throw away the pet. "

Wuhan Small Animal Protection Association: Foshan Dufan

On January 26, the Wuhan Small Animal Association promoted the "announcement of animal assistance to resident companion animals in their homes during the epidemic control period. ".

According to the Wuhan Small Animal Protection Association (Hereinafter referred to as "Wu Xiao Xie") statistics, only 26 and 27 days to the association sent help up to 400. On average, the association handles only about 50 requests a day. As of February 2, there was still a deluge of requests for help every day.

Three groups, 11 people, start processing callers at 8 a.m. each day, and Du leads his 10 teammates through Wuchang, Hankou, and Hanyang. The streets of the normally bustling city of Wuhan were quiet for a long time after the city was shut down. Public transport was shut down and people had to rely on themselves. "Even walking sideways on the street, no one cares about you, " Du joked.

A few days after the city was shut down in Wuhan, it rained heavily. Du originally planned to stop his voluntary activities, but Wuhan is far from being lifted, people in the city can't get out, people outside the city can't get in, and the pets left in the Han Dynasty are facing the situation of being starved to death. Many owners began to contact the association.

Du's original plan was broken. "We can't just wait, " he said. On January 26, Du, who coordinated from top to bottom, announced that he could throw food for the remaining Han's pets for free. In just two days, the information to seek help far exceeded du Fan's expectations, which was a big problem, not enough people.

The epidemic is getting worse and worse, and Wuhan is in a state of emergency. Du decided to keep the original 11-person team, focus on processing help information, in accordance with the "priority has been cut off" principle, arrange a sequence to come, and then start to contact the help, unlock the company, after the person asked for permission to open the door after the company to open the door to the pet after feeding in the witness to lock the door, this can go.

Wuhan Small Animal Protection Association Home Rescue Left Han pet

Even if we have been so careful, we still have to suffer a little. Volunteers are already at the door, but some have given up because of the cost of unlocking, watching their starving pets be abandoned by their owners. Whether you live or starve depends on a door, and inside is a life, and outside is cold money.

8:00 in the morning, 11:00 at night, 15 hours a day in the race of life.

After Wuhan's closure, many businesses have also launched paid cat feeding business, some businesses in social software on some of the pet unfortunate deaths in the Han Dynasty.

On Jan. 26, a delivery boy said he received a call after work. The owner asked for help to take care of his pet cat. When he came in, he found that the cat had given birth. Unfortunately, all the cats were dead.

"I just came in, my glasses were foggy, I couldn't see clearly, I thought the ground was a dead mouse, but it turned out to be a dead cat, " he wrote on Weibo. "The owner was sobbing when he spoke on Wechat. "

It's not just the rumors that hurt them

On January 29, Academician Li Lanjuan gave an interview to CCTV. In the interview was asked "can people infect pets? " , "can pets infect people after catching diseases? " And so on.

"If the pet does not come into contact with sick people or people with suspicious infections, then the pet is not sick and the quarantine is healthy, and that does not matter, " Li said. "because the disease (COVID-19) is transmitted from Mammal to Mammal, we should also take precautions against mammals. " "If the pet comes into contact with an epidemic or an infected person, then the pet should also be monitored. "

There have been a lot of articles and videos on the Internet saying that pets can also catch the new type of pneumonia. Many pet owners, instead of protecting their pets, have decided to throw them away. There are even local governments that issue animal kill documents.

Can pets spread disease? "there is no evidence that pets, such as dogs and cats, can be infected with COVID-19, " the WHO wrote in a Jan. 29 release. Washing hands with soap and water after contact with pets can significantly reduce the spread of other common bacteria between pets and humans, " the People's Daily wrote in a Jan. 29 article. "there is no evidence that this coronavirus will infect cats and dogs. "

As of February 2, the Wuhan Small Animal Association had received more than 700 requests for help, and the rescue operation has not been halted because of the ongoing outbreak.

The dream's plan is to tweet about the results of these days in early February, calling for more people to pay attention to small animals, in the hope of getting some funding in the future to rescue and adopt more stray animals.
